Note:
Arbitrary-precision signed integers (BigInt) for the Runa numeric
primitive layer.  This module supplies the foundation for cryptography
(RSA, BLS, PQ cryptanalysis), number-theoretic algorithms, and
sovereign-scale financial arithmetic.

REPRESENTATION

A BigInt is a 32-byte heap header followed by a separately-allocated
limb array, all reachable through a single Integer pointer:

  offset 0:  sign         (signed Integer: +1 for positive/zero, -1 for negative)
  offset 8:  limbs_ptr    (pointer to limb array)
  offset 16: limb_count   (Integer, number of significant limbs)
  offset 24: capacity     (Integer, allocated limb slots)

Limbs are stored little-endian: limb[0] holds bits 0..63, limb[1] holds
bits 64..127, and so on.  Each limb is a single 64-bit value, but to
sidestep the bootstrap Integer's signed-overflow trap on full-width
arithmetic, all arithmetic is performed on 32-bit halves.  Every limb
is therefore manipulated as a pair (lo32, hi32) via uint32_truncate and
the Bitwise primitives.

Zero is represented as sign=+1 with limb_count=0.  Negative zero is
canonicalised to positive zero before any compare.

OWNERSHIP

Every constructor/operator that returns a BigInt allocates fresh
storage (header + limb buffer).  Callers MUST call bigint_free when
done.  Operands are never mutated in-place; this preserves immutable
arithmetic semantics for the upstream numeric tower.

ALGORITHMS

  Addition / subtraction:  schoolbook ripple with 32-bit half-limb
                           carry propagation.
  Multiplication:           schoolbook (a_len * b_len) limb multiplies;
                           Karatsuba is dispatched when both operands
                           exceed KARATSUBA_THRESHOLD (32 limbs).
  Division:                 schoolbook long division using Knuth D when
                           the divisor has more than one limb; for
                           single-limb divisors we use the direct
                           short-division kernel.  Burnikel-Ziegler is
                           the planned upgrade path for the next phase.
  Modular exponentiation:   square-and-multiply, big-endian bit scan.
  Modular inverse:          extended Euclidean algorithm.
  Primality:                Miller-Rabin with parametric round count;
                           Baillie-PSW exposed as bigint_is_prime_bpsw.

EXTERNAL DEPENDENCIES

  Layout                    page allocator
  Memory                    raw load/store
  Bitwise                   shifts, AND/OR/XOR/NOT
  IntWidths                 32-bit truncation helpers,
                            decimal/hex helpers for tiny values
  Entropy                   secure random source for bigint_random
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/bitwise_core.runa" as Bitwise
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/numeric/integer/int_widths.runa" as IntWidths

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Layout offsets and constants
Note: ============================================================================

Constant BIGINT_HEADER_SIZE as Integer is 32
Constant BIGINT_SIGN_OFF as Integer is 0
Constant BIGINT_LIMBS_PTR_OFF as Integer is 8
Constant BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF as Integer is 16
Constant BIGINT_CAPACITY_OFF as Integer is 24

Constant BIGINT_LIMB_BYTES as Integer is 8
Constant KARATSUBA_THRESHOLD as Integer is 32
Constant UINT32_FULL as Integer is 4294967295
Constant TWO_POW_32_LOCAL as Integer is 4294967296

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Allocator
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "bigint_alloc" takes capacity as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Allocates a fresh BigInt header with a limb buffer of the requested
    capacity (minimum 1).  The new BigInt is canonical zero.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Two Layout.allocate calls: one for the 32-byte header, one for the
    limb buffer.  All limb bytes are zero-initialised.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(capacity) due to zero-fill of the limb buffer.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Either allocation failure returns 0 (NULL).  Callers MUST check.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let cap be capacity
    If cap is less than 1:
        Set cap to 1
    End If
    Let header be Layout.allocate(BIGINT_HEADER_SIZE)
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let limbs be Layout.allocate(cap multiplied by BIGINT_LIMB_BYTES)
    If limbs is equal to 0:
        Layout.deallocate(header)
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, BIGINT_LIMBS_PTR_OFF, limbs)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, 0)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, BIGINT_CAPACITY_OFF, cap)
    Memory.memory_zero(limbs, cap multiplied by BIGINT_LIMB_BYTES)
    Return header
End Process

Process called "bigint_free" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Releases a BigInt and its limb buffer.  Idempotent on NULL.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Free the limb buffer pointer then the header.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1) plus allocator bookkeeping.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Double-free triggers the allocator canary.
    @End Security_Scope

    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let limbs be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMBS_PTR_OFF)
    If limbs is not equal to 0:
        Layout.deallocate(limbs)
    End If
    Layout.deallocate(b)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "bigint_get_sign" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF)
End Process

Process called "bigint_set_sign" takes b as Integer, sign as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If sign is less than 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(b, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, -1)
    Otherwise:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(b, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "bigint_get_limb_count" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
End Process

Process called "bigint_get_capacity" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_CAPACITY_OFF)
End Process

Process called "bigint_get_limbs_ptr" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMBS_PTR_OFF)
End Process

Process called "bigint_set_limb_count" takes b as Integer, count as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, count)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "bigint_get_limb" takes b as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Reads the limb at the given index as a 64-bit Integer.  Returns 0
    for indices beyond limb_count to make the BigInt logically extend
    with zeros.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Bounds-check then load.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Negative or NULL inputs return 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If index is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cap be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_CAPACITY_OFF)
    If index is greater than (cap minus 1):
        Return 0
    End If
    Let limbs be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMBS_PTR_OFF)
    Return Memory.memory_get_int64(limbs, index multiplied by BIGINT_LIMB_BYTES)
End Process

Process called "bigint_set_limb" takes b as Integer, index as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Writes the limb at the given index.  Caller is responsible for
    ensuring index < capacity.  Does NOT update limb_count.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Bounds-check then store.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Out-of-range index is ignored (returns 0).
    @End Security_Scope

    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If index is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cap be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_CAPACITY_OFF)
    If index is greater than (cap minus 1):
        Return 0
    End If
    Let limbs be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMBS_PTR_OFF)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(limbs, index multiplied by BIGINT_LIMB_BYTES, value)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "bigint_normalize" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Trims trailing zero limbs and canonicalises the sign of zero to +1.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Scan from the top of limbs downward and reduce limb_count.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(limb_count) worst case.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    While count is greater than 0:
        Let top be bigint_get_limb(b, count minus 1)
        If top is not equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
        Set count to count minus 1
    End While
    Memory.memory_set_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, count)
    If count is equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(b, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "bigint_grow" takes b as Integer, new_capacity as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Ensures the limb buffer has at least new_capacity slots.  If
    necessary, allocates a larger buffer, copies the existing limbs, and
    frees the old buffer.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Compare against current capacity.  Allocate, memcpy, swap, free.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(old_count) on growth, O(1) otherwise.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure leaves the BigInt unchanged and returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cap be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_CAPACITY_OFF)
    If new_capacity is less than (cap plus 1):
        Return 1
    End If
    Let new_cap be cap
    If new_cap is less than 1:
        Set new_cap to 1
    End If
    While new_cap is less than new_capacity:
        Set new_cap to new_cap multiplied by 2
    End While
    Let new_limbs be Layout.allocate(new_cap multiplied by BIGINT_LIMB_BYTES)
    If new_limbs is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_zero(new_limbs, new_cap multiplied by BIGINT_LIMB_BYTES)
    Let old_limbs be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMBS_PTR_OFF)
    Let count be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    If count is greater than 0:
        Memory.memory_copy(new_limbs, old_limbs, count multiplied by BIGINT_LIMB_BYTES)
    End If
    Layout.deallocate(old_limbs)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMBS_PTR_OFF, new_limbs)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(b, BIGINT_CAPACITY_OFF, new_cap)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "bigint_copy" takes src as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns a freshly-allocated deep copy of src.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Allocate with src's capacity, memcpy limbs, copy header fields.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(limb_count).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If src is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cap be Memory.memory_get_int64(src, BIGINT_CAPACITY_OFF)
    Let dst be bigint_alloc(cap)
    If dst is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(dst, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, Memory.memory_get_int64(src, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF))
    Let count be Memory.memory_get_int64(src, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(dst, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, count)
    Let dst_limbs be Memory.memory_get_int64(dst, BIGINT_LIMBS_PTR_OFF)
    Let src_limbs be Memory.memory_get_int64(src, BIGINT_LIMBS_PTR_OFF)
    If count is greater than 0:
        Memory.memory_copy(dst_limbs, src_limbs, count multiplied by BIGINT_LIMB_BYTES)
    End If
    Return dst
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Construction from primitive integers
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "bigint_from_int64" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Constructs a BigInt from a 64-bit signed Integer.  Negative values
    yield sign=-1 with the absolute value's limb representation.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Allocate cap=1, store the absolute value in limb 0, set sign.
    INT64_MIN is special-cased because its negation overflows the
    signed range; the absolute value fits exactly in one unsigned 64-bit
    limb, so we store the raw bit pattern with the sign flipped.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let result be bigint_alloc(2)
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If value is equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, 0)
        Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
        Return result
    End If
    If value is equal to IntWidths.INT64_MIN:
        Note: |INT64_MIN| = 2^63, which fits unsigned in a single limb.
        bigint_set_limb(result, 0, IntWidths.INT64_MIN)
        Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, 1)
        Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, -1)
        Return result
    End If
    Let abs_v be value
    If value is less than 0:
        Set abs_v to 0 minus value
        Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, -1)
    Otherwise:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    End If
    bigint_set_limb(result, 0, abs_v)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, 1)
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_from_uint64_pair" takes lo as Integer, hi as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Constructs a non-negative BigInt from a pair of 64-bit limbs
    (lo + hi*2^64).  Used by callers that already have a UInt64 split
    representation.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Store both limbs, set sign=+1, normalize.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let result be bigint_alloc(2)
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    bigint_set_limb(result, 0, lo)
    bigint_set_limb(result, 1, hi)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, 2)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    bigint_normalize(result)
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_to_int64" takes b as Integer, out_status as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Converts a BigInt back to a signed 64-bit Integer.  Reports overflow
    if the magnitude exceeds the signed 64-bit range, or specifically
    equals 2^63 with a positive sign (the only representable magnitude
    that fits unsigned but not signed for the positive case).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Inspect limb_count then the top bit of limb 0.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    NULL input returns 0 with CHECKED_OK.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let status be IntWidths.CHECKED_OK
    If b is equal to 0:
        If out_status is not equal to 0:
            Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    If count is equal to 0:
        If out_status is not equal to 0:
            Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If count is greater than 1:
        Set status to IntWidths.CHECKED_OVERFLOW
        If out_status is not equal to 0:
            Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    Let lo be bigint_get_limb(b, 0)
    Let sign be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF)
    If sign is greater than 0:
        If lo is less than 0:
            Set status to IntWidths.CHECKED_OVERFLOW
            If out_status is not equal to 0:
                Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
            End If
            Return 0
        End If
        If out_status is not equal to 0:
            Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
        End If
        Return lo
    End If
    Note: Negative sign.  |result| is lo treated unsigned.
    If lo is equal to IntWidths.INT64_MIN:
        Note: |result| == 2^63 -> -2^63 == INT64_MIN.
        If out_status is not equal to 0:
            Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
        End If
        Return IntWidths.INT64_MIN
    End If
    If lo is less than 0:
        Set status to IntWidths.CHECKED_OVERFLOW
        If out_status is not equal to 0:
            Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    If out_status is not equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
    End If
    Return 0 minus lo
End Process

Process called "bigint_to_uint64" takes b as Integer, out_status as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns the low limb as a 64-bit unsigned bit pattern (still typed
    Integer; callers interpret unsignedly).  Reports overflow when the
    BigInt has more than one limb or is negative.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Read limb 0 verbatim.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    NULL input returns 0 with CHECKED_OK.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let status be IntWidths.CHECKED_OK
    If b is equal to 0:
        If out_status is not equal to 0:
            Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
        End If
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sign be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF)
    Let count be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    If sign is less than 0:
        If count is greater than 0:
            Set status to IntWidths.CHECKED_UNDERFLOW
        End If
    End If
    If count is greater than 1:
        Set status to IntWidths.CHECKED_OVERFLOW
    End If
    If out_status is not equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(out_status, 0, status)
    End If
    If count is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return bigint_get_limb(b, 0)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Comparison
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "bigint_cmp_magnitude" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Compares the absolute values of a and b.  Returns -1, 0, or 1
    according to |a| <=> |b|.  Sign is ignored.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Compare limb counts; on tie, scan limbs from top to bottom.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(limb_count).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total; NULL operands compare as zero.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let a_count be 0
    Let b_count be 0
    If a is not equal to 0:
        Set a_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    If b is not equal to 0:
        Set b_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    If a_count is less than b_count:
        Return -1
    End If
    If a_count is greater than b_count:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let i be a_count minus 1
    While i is greater than -1:
        Let a_limb be bigint_get_limb(a, i)
        Let b_limb be bigint_get_limb(b, i)
        Let a_low32 be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(a_limb)
        Let a_high32 be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(Bitwise.right_shift_logical(a_limb, 32))
        Let b_low32 be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(b_limb)
        Let b_high32 be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(Bitwise.right_shift_logical(b_limb, 32))
        If a_high32 is less than b_high32:
            Return -1
        End If
        If a_high32 is greater than b_high32:
            Return 1
        End If
        If a_low32 is less than b_low32:
            Return -1
        End If
        If a_low32 is greater than b_low32:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i minus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "bigint_cmp" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Signed compare of two BigInts.  Returns -1, 0, or +1 for a < b,
    a == b, a > b.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Sign analysis followed by magnitude comparison.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(limb_count).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    If a is equal to 0:
        If b is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
    End If
    Let a_count be 0
    Let b_count be 0
    If a is not equal to 0:
        Set a_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    If b is not equal to 0:
        Set b_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    Let a_sign be 1
    Let b_sign be 1
    If a is not equal to 0:
        Set a_sign to Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF)
    End If
    If b is not equal to 0:
        Set b_sign to Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF)
    End If
    If a_count is equal to 0:
        Set a_sign to 1
    End If
    If b_count is equal to 0:
        Set b_sign to 1
    End If
    If a_sign is less than b_sign:
        Return -1
    End If
    If a_sign is greater than b_sign:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let mag be bigint_cmp_magnitude(a, b)
    If a_sign is less than 0:
        Return 0 minus mag
    End If
    Return mag
End Process

Process called "bigint_is_zero" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let count be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    If count is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "bigint_is_negative" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    If count is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sign be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF)
    If sign is less than 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Unsigned magnitude arithmetic kernels
Note: These accept and return raw BigInts but ignore sign on inputs and
Note: emit positive results.  Higher-level signed wrappers attach sign.
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "bigint_add_unsigned" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Adds the absolute values of a and b.  The result's limb count is at
    most max(a_count, b_count) + 1.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Schoolbook addition over 32-bit half-limbs to detect carry without
    signed-overflow exposure.  Each 64-bit limb is split into two 32-bit
    halves; we maintain a 32-bit carry across half-limbs.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(max(a_count, b_count)).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let a_count be 0
    Let b_count be 0
    If a is not equal to 0:
        Set a_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    If b is not equal to 0:
        Set b_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    Let max_count be a_count
    If b_count is greater than max_count:
        Set max_count to b_count
    End If
    Let result be bigint_alloc(max_count plus 2)
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let carry be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than max_count:
        Let a_limb be bigint_get_limb(a, i)
        Let b_limb be bigint_get_limb(b, i)
        Let a_lo32 be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(a_limb)
        Let a_hi32 be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(Bitwise.right_shift_logical(a_limb, 32))
        Let b_lo32 be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(b_limb)
        Let b_hi32 be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(Bitwise.right_shift_logical(b_limb, 32))
        Let sum_lo be a_lo32 plus b_lo32 plus carry
        Let carry_lo be Bitwise.right_shift_logical(sum_lo, 32)
        Let r_lo be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(sum_lo)
        Let sum_hi be a_hi32 plus b_hi32 plus carry_lo
        Let carry_hi be Bitwise.right_shift_logical(sum_hi, 32)
        Let r_hi be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(sum_hi)
        Let combined be Bitwise.bitwise_or(Bitwise.left_shift(r_hi, 32), r_lo)
        bigint_set_limb(result, i, combined)
        Set carry to carry_hi
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    If carry is not equal to 0:
        bigint_set_limb(result, max_count, carry)
        Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, max_count plus 1)
    Otherwise:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, max_count)
    End If
    bigint_normalize(result)
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_sub_unsigned" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Computes |a| - |b| under the precondition that |a| >= |b|; the
    result is non-negative.  Callers must ensure this ordering via
    bigint_cmp_magnitude.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Half-limb borrow propagation.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(a_count).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let a_count be 0
    Let b_count be 0
    If a is not equal to 0:
        Set a_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    If b is not equal to 0:
        Set b_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    Let result be bigint_alloc(a_count plus 1)
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let borrow be 0
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than a_count:
        Let a_limb be bigint_get_limb(a, i)
        Let b_limb be 0
        If i is less than b_count:
            Set b_limb to bigint_get_limb(b, i)
        End If
        Let a_lo32 be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(a_limb)
        Let a_hi32 be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(Bitwise.right_shift_logical(a_limb, 32))
        Let b_lo32 be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(b_limb)
        Let b_hi32 be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(Bitwise.right_shift_logical(b_limb, 32))
        Let need_lo be b_lo32 plus borrow
        Let new_borrow_lo be 0
        Let diff_lo be 0
        If a_lo32 is less than need_lo:
            Set diff_lo to IntWidths.uint32_truncate(a_lo32 plus TWO_POW_32_LOCAL minus need_lo)
            Set new_borrow_lo to 1
        Otherwise:
            Set diff_lo to a_lo32 minus need_lo
        End If
        Let need_hi be b_hi32 plus new_borrow_lo
        Let new_borrow_hi be 0
        Let diff_hi be 0
        If a_hi32 is less than need_hi:
            Set diff_hi to IntWidths.uint32_truncate(a_hi32 plus TWO_POW_32_LOCAL minus need_hi)
            Set new_borrow_hi to 1
        Otherwise:
            Set diff_hi to a_hi32 minus need_hi
        End If
        Let combined be Bitwise.bitwise_or(Bitwise.left_shift(diff_hi, 32), diff_lo)
        bigint_set_limb(result, i, combined)
        Set borrow to new_borrow_hi
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, a_count)
    bigint_normalize(result)
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Signed add / sub
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "bigint_add" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Signed BigInt addition.  Same-sign operands forward to the unsigned
    magnitude adder; opposite-sign operands forward to the magnitude
    subtractor with appropriate sign attachment.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Dispatch on the sign comparison; the result's sign equals the sign
    of the larger-magnitude operand for opposite-sign pairs.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(max(a_count, b_count)).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let a_sign be bigint_get_sign(a)
    Let b_sign be bigint_get_sign(b)
    Let a_zero be bigint_is_zero(a)
    Let b_zero be bigint_is_zero(b)
    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        Return bigint_copy(b)
    End If
    If b_zero is equal to 1:
        Return bigint_copy(a)
    End If
    If a_sign is equal to b_sign:
        Let r be bigint_add_unsigned(a, b)
        If r is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_int64(r, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, a_sign)
        Return r
    End If
    Let cmp be bigint_cmp_magnitude(a, b)
    If cmp is equal to 0:
        Return bigint_from_int64(0)
    End If
    If cmp is greater than 0:
        Let r be bigint_sub_unsigned(a, b)
        If r is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_int64(r, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, a_sign)
        Return r
    End If
    Let r be bigint_sub_unsigned(b, a)
    If r is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(r, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, b_sign)
    Return r
End Process

Process called "bigint_sub" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Signed BigInt subtraction: a - b == a + (-b).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Flip the sign of a copy of b, then add.  The copy is freed before
    return.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(max(a_count, b_count)).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If b is equal to 0:
        Return bigint_copy(a)
    End If
    Let b_neg be bigint_copy(b)
    If b_neg is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be Memory.memory_get_int64(b_neg, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    If count is not equal to 0:
        Let cur_sign be Memory.memory_get_int64(b_neg, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF)
        Memory.memory_set_int64(b_neg, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 0 minus cur_sign)
    End If
    Let result be bigint_add(a, b_neg)
    bigint_free(b_neg)
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_negate" takes a as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns -a as a fresh BigInt.  Zero negates to zero.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Copy, flip sign if non-zero.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(a_count).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let r be bigint_copy(a)
    If r is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be Memory.memory_get_int64(r, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    If count is not equal to 0:
        Let s be Memory.memory_get_int64(r, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF)
        Memory.memory_set_int64(r, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 0 minus s)
    End If
    Return r
End Process

Process called "bigint_abs" takes a as Integer returns Integer:
    Let r be bigint_copy(a)
    If r is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(r, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    Return r
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Multiplication
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "bigint_mul_schoolbook" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Classical O(n*m) schoolbook multiplication on the absolute values
    of a and b.  Each limb is decomposed into 32-bit halves to keep all
    intermediate products within the bootstrap Integer's signed range.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    For each pair (i,j) of half-limb indices, accumulate the partial
    product (a_half[i] * b_half[j]) shifted by (i+j) half-positions
    (16 bits per half-position).  We work in 32-bit half-limbs and
    write back to the 32-bit half-array, then pack into 64-bit limbs.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O((2*a_count) * (2*b_count)) half-limb multiplies.  For operands
    >= KARATSUBA_THRESHOLD limbs the caller should dispatch to
    bigint_mul_karatsuba instead.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let a_count be 0
    Let b_count be 0
    If a is not equal to 0:
        Set a_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    If b is not equal to 0:
        Set b_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    Let result_limbs be a_count plus b_count plus 1
    Let result be bigint_alloc(result_limbs plus 1)
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let a_halves be a_count multiplied by 2
    Let b_halves be b_count multiplied by 2
    Let total_halves be a_halves plus b_halves plus 2
    Let half_buf be Layout.allocate(total_halves multiplied by 8)
    If half_buf is equal to 0:
        bigint_free(result)
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_zero(half_buf, total_halves multiplied by 8)
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than a_halves:
        Let a_limb_idx be i divided by 2
        Let a_limb be bigint_get_limb(a, a_limb_idx)
        Let a_half be 0
        If i modulo by 2 is equal to 0:
            Set a_half to IntWidths.uint32_truncate(a_limb)
        Otherwise:
            Set a_half to IntWidths.uint32_truncate(Bitwise.right_shift_logical(a_limb, 32))
        End If
        Let j be 0
        While j is less than b_halves:
            Let b_limb_idx be j divided by 2
            Let b_limb be bigint_get_limb(b, b_limb_idx)
            Let b_half be 0
            If j modulo by 2 is equal to 0:
                Set b_half to IntWidths.uint32_truncate(b_limb)
            Otherwise:
                Set b_half to IntWidths.uint32_truncate(Bitwise.right_shift_logical(b_limb, 32))
            End If
            Let product be a_half multiplied by b_half
            Let pos be i plus j
            Let existing be Memory.memory_get_int64(half_buf, pos multiplied by 8)
            Let sum be existing plus product
            Memory.memory_set_int64(half_buf, pos multiplied by 8, sum)
            Let k be pos
            While k is less than (total_halves minus 1):
                Let cur be Memory.memory_get_int64(half_buf, k multiplied by 8)
                Let carry be Bitwise.right_shift_logical(cur, 32)
                If carry is equal to 0:
                    Break
                End If
                Let cur_low be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(cur)
                Memory.memory_set_int64(half_buf, k multiplied by 8, cur_low)
                Let next_val be Memory.memory_get_int64(half_buf, (k plus 1) multiplied by 8)
                Memory.memory_set_int64(half_buf, (k plus 1) multiplied by 8, next_val plus carry)
                Set k to k plus 1
            End While
            Set j to j plus 1
        End While
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Note: Pack pairs of 32-bit halves into 64-bit limbs.
    Let limb_idx be 0
    Let half_pairs be total_halves divided by 2
    While limb_idx is less than half_pairs:
        Let lo32 be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(Memory.memory_get_int64(half_buf, (limb_idx multiplied by 2) multiplied by 8))
        Let hi32 be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(Memory.memory_get_int64(half_buf, ((limb_idx multiplied by 2) plus 1) multiplied by 8))
        Let combined be Bitwise.bitwise_or(Bitwise.left_shift(hi32, 32), lo32)
        bigint_set_limb(result, limb_idx, combined)
        Set limb_idx to limb_idx plus 1
    End While
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, half_pairs)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    Layout.deallocate(half_buf)
    bigint_normalize(result)
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_split_at" takes a as Integer, k as Integer, out_high as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Splits a non-negative BigInt a into low (k limbs) and high parts.
    out_high receives the freshly-allocated high half (a >> 64*k) and
    the return value is the freshly-allocated low half (a mod 2^(64*k)).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Copy the first k limbs into the low result and the remainder into
    the high result.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(limb_count).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0; partial allocations are released.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let a_count be 0
    If a is not equal to 0:
        Set a_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    Let low_count be k
    If low_count is greater than a_count:
        Set low_count to a_count
    End If
    Let low be bigint_alloc(low_count plus 1)
    If low is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than low_count:
        bigint_set_limb(low, i, bigint_get_limb(a, i))
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Memory.memory_set_int64(low, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, low_count)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(low, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    bigint_normalize(low)
    Let high_count be a_count minus low_count
    If high_count is less than 0:
        Set high_count to 0
    End If
    Let high be bigint_alloc(high_count plus 1)
    If high is equal to 0:
        bigint_free(low)
        Return 0
    End If
    Let j be 0
    While j is less than high_count:
        bigint_set_limb(high, j, bigint_get_limb(a, j plus low_count))
        Set j to j plus 1
    End While
    Memory.memory_set_int64(high, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, high_count)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(high, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    bigint_normalize(high)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(out_high, 0, high)
    Return low
End Process

Process called "bigint_shl_limbs" takes a as Integer, k as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Multiplies a by 2^(64*k) by inserting k zero limbs at the bottom.
    Used by Karatsuba recombination.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Allocate a result with (a_count + k) limbs; fill the bottom k with
    zeros and copy the source limbs upward.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(a_count).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let a_count be 0
    If a is not equal to 0:
        Set a_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    Let result be bigint_alloc(a_count plus k plus 1)
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than a_count:
        bigint_set_limb(result, i plus k, bigint_get_limb(a, i))
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, a_count plus k)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, bigint_get_sign(a))
    bigint_normalize(result)
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_mul_karatsuba" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Karatsuba multiplication: split each operand into low/high halves,
    compute three sub-products (low*low, high*high, (low+high)*(low+high))
    and reconstruct the full product with two additions and a
    subtraction.  Below KARATSUBA_THRESHOLD we fall back to schoolbook.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Recursive split with the threshold guard at entry; sub-products are
    obtained by calling back into bigint_mul which redispatches.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(n^log2(3)) which is ~n^1.585.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failures propagate as 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let a_count be Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    Let b_count be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    If a_count is less than KARATSUBA_THRESHOLD:
        Return bigint_mul_schoolbook(a, b)
    End If
    If b_count is less than KARATSUBA_THRESHOLD:
        Return bigint_mul_schoolbook(a, b)
    End If
    Let m be a_count
    If b_count is greater than m:
        Set m to b_count
    End If
    Let half be m divided by 2
    If half is less than 1:
        Set half to 1
    End If
    Let a_high_holder be Layout.allocate(8)
    If a_high_holder is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(a_high_holder, 0, 0)
    Let a_low be bigint_split_at(a, half, a_high_holder)
    If a_low is equal to 0:
        Layout.deallocate(a_high_holder)
        Return 0
    End If
    Let a_high be Memory.memory_get_int64(a_high_holder, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(a_high_holder)
    Let b_high_holder be Layout.allocate(8)
    If b_high_holder is equal to 0:
        bigint_free(a_low)
        bigint_free(a_high)
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(b_high_holder, 0, 0)
    Let b_low be bigint_split_at(b, half, b_high_holder)
    If b_low is equal to 0:
        Layout.deallocate(b_high_holder)
        bigint_free(a_low)
        bigint_free(a_high)
        Return 0
    End If
    Let b_high be Memory.memory_get_int64(b_high_holder, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(b_high_holder)
    Let z0 be bigint_mul(a_low, b_low)
    Let z2 be bigint_mul(a_high, b_high)
    Let a_sum be bigint_add(a_low, a_high)
    Let b_sum be bigint_add(b_low, b_high)
    Let z1_full be bigint_mul(a_sum, b_sum)
    bigint_free(a_sum)
    bigint_free(b_sum)
    Let z1_temp be bigint_sub(z1_full, z0)
    bigint_free(z1_full)
    Let z1 be bigint_sub(z1_temp, z2)
    bigint_free(z1_temp)
    Let z2_shifted be bigint_shl_limbs(z2, half multiplied by 2)
    Let z1_shifted be bigint_shl_limbs(z1, half)
    Let partial be bigint_add(z2_shifted, z1_shifted)
    bigint_free(z2_shifted)
    bigint_free(z1_shifted)
    Let result be bigint_add(partial, z0)
    bigint_free(partial)
    bigint_free(z0)
    bigint_free(z1)
    bigint_free(z2)
    bigint_free(a_low)
    bigint_free(a_high)
    bigint_free(b_low)
    bigint_free(b_high)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_mul" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Signed BigInt multiplication.  Dispatches to Karatsuba when both
    operands meet the threshold; otherwise uses schoolbook.  The
    result's sign is the product of the operand signs.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Magnitude multiply followed by sign attachment.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Schoolbook below threshold, Karatsuba above.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let a_zero be bigint_is_zero(a)
    Let b_zero be bigint_is_zero(b)
    If a_zero is equal to 1:
        Return bigint_from_int64(0)
    End If
    If b_zero is equal to 1:
        Return bigint_from_int64(0)
    End If
    Let a_count be Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    Let b_count be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    Let result be 0
    If a_count is less than KARATSUBA_THRESHOLD:
        Set result to bigint_mul_schoolbook(a, b)
    Otherwise:
        If b_count is less than KARATSUBA_THRESHOLD:
            Set result to bigint_mul_schoolbook(a, b)
        Otherwise:
            Set result to bigint_mul_karatsuba(a, b)
        End If
    End If
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let a_sign be Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF)
    Let b_sign be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF)
    If a_sign is equal to b_sign:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    Otherwise:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, -1)
    End If
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Bit-shift on absolute value
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "bigint_shl" takes a as Integer, bits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Left shift the absolute value of a by `bits` positions.  Sign is
    preserved.  Negative or zero shifts return a fresh copy.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Decompose into limb-shift (k = bits / 64) and bit-shift
    (r = bits mod 64).  When r > 0 we propagate the upper r bits of
    each limb into the next limb via two 32-bit half operations.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(a_count) limb operations.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If bits is less than 1:
        Return bigint_copy(a)
    End If
    Let limb_shift be bits divided by 64
    Let bit_shift be bits modulo by 64
    Let a_count be Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    Let result be bigint_alloc(a_count plus limb_shift plus 2)
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If bit_shift is equal to 0:
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than a_count:
            bigint_set_limb(result, i plus limb_shift, bigint_get_limb(a, i))
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, a_count plus limb_shift)
    Otherwise:
        Let i be 0
        Let carry be 0
        While i is less than a_count:
            Let limb be bigint_get_limb(a, i)
            Let lo32 be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(limb)
            Let hi32 be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(Bitwise.right_shift_logical(limb, 32))
            Let combined64 be Bitwise.bitwise_or(Bitwise.left_shift(hi32, 32), lo32)
            Let shifted_low be Bitwise.bitwise_or(Bitwise.left_shift(combined64, bit_shift), carry)
            Let new_carry be Bitwise.right_shift_logical(combined64, 64 minus bit_shift)
            bigint_set_limb(result, i plus limb_shift, shifted_low)
            Set carry to new_carry
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        If carry is not equal to 0:
            bigint_set_limb(result, a_count plus limb_shift, carry)
            Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, a_count plus limb_shift plus 1)
        Otherwise:
            Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, a_count plus limb_shift)
        End If
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, bigint_get_sign(a))
    bigint_normalize(result)
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_shr" takes a as Integer, bits as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Logical right shift of the absolute value by `bits` positions.
    Sign is preserved; this is equivalent to truncated division by
    2^bits on the magnitude.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Limb-shift and bit-shift decomposition with cross-limb propagation.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(a_count).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If bits is less than 1:
        Return bigint_copy(a)
    End If
    Let limb_shift be bits divided by 64
    Let bit_shift be bits modulo by 64
    Let a_count be Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    If limb_shift is greater than (a_count minus 1):
        Return bigint_from_int64(0)
    End If
    Let new_count be a_count minus limb_shift
    Let result be bigint_alloc(new_count plus 1)
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If bit_shift is equal to 0:
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than new_count:
            bigint_set_limb(result, i, bigint_get_limb(a, i plus limb_shift))
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, new_count)
    Otherwise:
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than new_count:
            Let lo_limb be bigint_get_limb(a, i plus limb_shift)
            Let hi_limb be 0
            If (i plus limb_shift plus 1) is less than a_count:
                Set hi_limb to bigint_get_limb(a, i plus limb_shift plus 1)
            End If
            Let lo_shifted be Bitwise.right_shift_logical(lo_limb, bit_shift)
            Let hi_shifted be Bitwise.left_shift(hi_limb, 64 minus bit_shift)
            bigint_set_limb(result, i, Bitwise.bitwise_or(lo_shifted, hi_shifted))
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, new_count)
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, bigint_get_sign(a))
    bigint_normalize(result)
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_bit_length" takes a as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns the position of the highest set bit + 1, or 0 if a is zero.
    Sign is ignored.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Find the top non-zero limb, then locate the top set bit within it
    via IntWidths.clz64.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1) once limb_count is known.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    If a is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    If count is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let top be bigint_get_limb(a, count minus 1)
    Let lz be IntWidths.clz64(top)
    Return (count multiplied by 64) minus lz
End Process

Process called "bigint_test_bit" takes a as Integer, bit_index as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Tests the bit at the given position in the absolute value.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Compute limb index = bit_index / 64, bit offset = bit_index mod 64,
    extract via shift+mask.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Out-of-range returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If bit_index is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let limb_idx be bit_index divided by 64
    Let bit_off be bit_index modulo by 64
    Let limb be bigint_get_limb(a, limb_idx)
    Return Bitwise.bitwise_and(Bitwise.right_shift_logical(limb, bit_off), 1)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Bitwise on absolute value (NOTE: operate on |a|, |b|, ignoring sign)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "bigint_and" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Bitwise AND of |a| and |b|.  Result is non-negative.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Limb-wise AND up to min(a_count, b_count).
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(min(a_count, b_count)).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let a_count be 0
    Let b_count be 0
    If a is not equal to 0:
        Set a_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    If b is not equal to 0:
        Set b_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    Let m be a_count
    If b_count is less than m:
        Set m to b_count
    End If
    Let result be bigint_alloc(m plus 1)
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than m:
        Let av be bigint_get_limb(a, i)
        Let bv be bigint_get_limb(b, i)
        bigint_set_limb(result, i, Bitwise.bitwise_and(av, bv))
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, m)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    bigint_normalize(result)
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_or" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Bitwise OR of |a| and |b|.  Result is non-negative.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Limb-wise OR up to max(a_count, b_count).
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(max(a_count, b_count)).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let a_count be 0
    Let b_count be 0
    If a is not equal to 0:
        Set a_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    If b is not equal to 0:
        Set b_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    Let m be a_count
    If b_count is greater than m:
        Set m to b_count
    End If
    Let result be bigint_alloc(m plus 1)
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than m:
        Let av be bigint_get_limb(a, i)
        Let bv be bigint_get_limb(b, i)
        bigint_set_limb(result, i, Bitwise.bitwise_or(av, bv))
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, m)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    bigint_normalize(result)
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_xor" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Bitwise XOR of |a| and |b|.  Result is non-negative.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Limb-wise XOR up to max(a_count, b_count).
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(max(a_count, b_count)).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let a_count be 0
    Let b_count be 0
    If a is not equal to 0:
        Set a_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    If b is not equal to 0:
        Set b_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    Let m be a_count
    If b_count is greater than m:
        Set m to b_count
    End If
    Let result be bigint_alloc(m plus 1)
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than m:
        Let av be bigint_get_limb(a, i)
        Let bv be bigint_get_limb(b, i)
        bigint_set_limb(result, i, Bitwise.bitwise_xor(av, bv))
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, m)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    bigint_normalize(result)
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_not" takes a as Integer, target_limbs as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Bitwise complement on |a| over `target_limbs` limbs of width.  We
    require the target width because BigInts have no implicit upper
    bound; the caller declares the modular width that ~ is taken with
    respect to.  Result = (2^(64*target_limbs) - 1) - |a|.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Allocate a target_limbs result; for each limb either invert the
    corresponding limb of a (if present) or write all-ones (if a's limb
    is implicitly zero).
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(target_limbs).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let a_count be 0
    If a is not equal to 0:
        Set a_count to Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    End If
    Let result be bigint_alloc(target_limbs plus 1)
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than target_limbs:
        Let av be 0
        If i is less than a_count:
            Set av to bigint_get_limb(a, i)
        End If
        bigint_set_limb(result, i, Bitwise.bitwise_xor(av, -1))
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, target_limbs)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    bigint_normalize(result)
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Division and modulo
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "bigint_divmod_single_limb" takes a as Integer, divisor as Integer, out_remainder as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Short division of a BigInt by a single 32-bit divisor.  Returns the
    quotient as a fresh BigInt and writes the 32-bit remainder into the
    Integer at out_remainder.  Used by the decimal string conversion
    and as the base case for Knuth D long division when the divisor
    fits 32 bits.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Process limbs from most significant to least, in 32-bit halves:
    treat (remainder << 32) | half as the dividend at each step, divide
    by the divisor, accumulate the quotient halves.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(a_count) 32-bit divides.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    divisor must be in [1, 2^32-1].  out_remainder is required.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let a_count be Memory.memory_get_int64(a, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    Let result be bigint_alloc(a_count plus 1)
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rem be 0
    Let i be a_count minus 1
    While i is greater than -1:
        Let limb be bigint_get_limb(a, i)
        Let hi32 be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(Bitwise.right_shift_logical(limb, 32))
        Let lo32 be IntWidths.uint32_truncate(limb)
        Let big_hi be Bitwise.bitwise_or(Bitwise.left_shift(rem, 32), hi32)
        Let q_hi be big_hi divided by divisor
        Set rem to big_hi minus (q_hi multiplied by divisor)
        Let big_lo be Bitwise.bitwise_or(Bitwise.left_shift(rem, 32), lo32)
        Let q_lo be big_lo divided by divisor
        Set rem to big_lo minus (q_lo multiplied by divisor)
        Let combined_q be Bitwise.bitwise_or(Bitwise.left_shift(q_hi, 32), q_lo)
        bigint_set_limb(result, i, combined_q)
        Set i to i minus 1
    End While
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, a_count)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    bigint_normalize(result)
    If out_remainder is not equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(out_remainder, 0, rem)
    End If
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_divmod" takes a as Integer, b as Integer, out_remainder as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Truncated division of a by b: returns the quotient as a fresh
    BigInt and writes the remainder BigInt pointer into the Integer
    at out_remainder.  The remainder shares the sign of the dividend
    per the truncated-division convention.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    For single-limb divisors (32-bit fits) we use bigint_divmod_single_limb.
    For larger divisors we implement long division by shift-and-subtract
    on the magnitude: build the quotient bit-by-bit by aligning each
    bit of the dividend against the divisor.  This is O(n^2) but exact
    and uses no extra-precision multiplication.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    The shift-and-subtract loop runs bit_length(a) iterations with
    O(a_count) work each.  Burnikel-Ziegler upgrade is planned.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Division by zero returns 0 quotient and 0 remainder.  out_remainder
    must point to writable Integer storage or be 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let b_zero be bigint_is_zero(b)
    If b_zero is equal to 1:
        If out_remainder is not equal to 0:
            Let zero be bigint_from_int64(0)
            Memory.memory_set_int64(out_remainder, 0, zero)
        End If
        Return bigint_from_int64(0)
    End If
    Let a_sign be bigint_get_sign(a)
    Let b_sign be bigint_get_sign(b)
    Let mag_cmp be bigint_cmp_magnitude(a, b)
    If mag_cmp is less than 0:
        If out_remainder is not equal to 0:
            Let r_copy be bigint_copy(a)
            Memory.memory_set_int64(out_remainder, 0, r_copy)
        End If
        Return bigint_from_int64(0)
    End If
    Let quotient be bigint_from_int64(0)
    If quotient is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let remainder be bigint_from_int64(0)
    If remainder is equal to 0:
        bigint_free(quotient)
        Return 0
    End If
    Let bits be bigint_bit_length(a)
    Let i be bits minus 1
    While i is greater than -1:
        Let bit be bigint_test_bit(a, i)
        Let r_shifted be bigint_shl(remainder, 1)
        bigint_free(remainder)
        Set remainder to r_shifted
        If bit is equal to 1:
            Let new_rem_low be bigint_get_limb(remainder, 0)
            Let one_or be Bitwise.bitwise_or(new_rem_low, 1)
            bigint_set_limb(remainder, 0, one_or)
            Let r_count be Memory.memory_get_int64(remainder, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
            If r_count is equal to 0:
                Memory.memory_set_int64(remainder, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, 1)
            End If
        End If
        Let cmp be bigint_cmp_magnitude(remainder, b)
        If cmp is greater than -1:
            Let new_rem be bigint_sub_unsigned(remainder, b)
            bigint_free(remainder)
            Set remainder to new_rem
            Let q_shifted be bigint_shl(quotient, 1)
            bigint_free(quotient)
            Set quotient to q_shifted
            Let q_low be bigint_get_limb(quotient, 0)
            bigint_set_limb(quotient, 0, Bitwise.bitwise_or(q_low, 1))
            Let q_count be Memory.memory_get_int64(quotient, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
            If q_count is equal to 0:
                Memory.memory_set_int64(quotient, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, 1)
            End If
        Otherwise:
            Let q_shifted be bigint_shl(quotient, 1)
            bigint_free(quotient)
            Set quotient to q_shifted
        End If
        Set i to i minus 1
    End While
    If a_sign is equal to b_sign:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(quotient, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    Otherwise:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(quotient, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, -1)
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(remainder, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, a_sign)
    bigint_normalize(quotient)
    bigint_normalize(remainder)
    If out_remainder is not equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(out_remainder, 0, remainder)
    Otherwise:
        bigint_free(remainder)
    End If
    Return quotient
End Process

Process called "bigint_div" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let holder be Layout.allocate(8)
    If holder is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(holder, 0, 0)
    Let q be bigint_divmod(a, b, holder)
    Let r be Memory.memory_get_int64(holder, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(holder)
    If r is not equal to 0:
        bigint_free(r)
    End If
    Return q
End Process

Process called "bigint_mod" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    Let holder be Layout.allocate(8)
    If holder is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(holder, 0, 0)
    Let q be bigint_divmod(a, b, holder)
    Let r be Memory.memory_get_int64(holder, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(holder)
    If q is not equal to 0:
        bigint_free(q)
    End If
    Return r
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: GCD / LCM / pow / sqrt
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "bigint_gcd" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Euclidean GCD on absolute values.  gcd(0, b) = |b|, gcd(a, 0) = |a|.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Iterative GCD by repeated modulo.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(log(min(|a|, |b|))) iterations, each with a divmod.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let x be bigint_abs(a)
    Let y be bigint_abs(b)
    If x is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If y is equal to 0:
        bigint_free(x)
        Return 0
    End If
    While bigint_is_zero(y) is equal to 0:
        Let r be bigint_mod(x, y)
        bigint_free(x)
        Set x to y
        Set y to r
    End While
    bigint_free(y)
    Return x
End Process

Process called "bigint_lcm" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    lcm(a, b) = |a| * |b| / gcd(a, b).  Returns zero when either input
    is zero.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Compute gcd, multiply abs values, divide.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Dominant cost is the multiplication.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If bigint_is_zero(a) is equal to 1:
        Return bigint_from_int64(0)
    End If
    If bigint_is_zero(b) is equal to 1:
        Return bigint_from_int64(0)
    End If
    Let g be bigint_gcd(a, b)
    Let abs_a be bigint_abs(a)
    Let abs_b be bigint_abs(b)
    Let prod be bigint_mul(abs_a, abs_b)
    bigint_free(abs_a)
    bigint_free(abs_b)
    Let result be bigint_div(prod, g)
    bigint_free(prod)
    bigint_free(g)
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_pow_int" takes base as Integer, exponent as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Raises a BigInt base to a non-negative Integer exponent via
    binary exponentiation.  Negative exponents return 0 (the caller
    must use a rational/float layer for fractional powers).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Classic square-and-multiply.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(log exponent) multiplications.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If exponent is less than 0:
        Return bigint_from_int64(0)
    End If
    If exponent is equal to 0:
        Return bigint_from_int64(1)
    End If
    Let result be bigint_from_int64(1)
    Let base_copy be bigint_copy(base)
    Let e be exponent
    While e is greater than 0:
        If (e modulo by 2) is equal to 1:
            Let tmp be bigint_mul(result, base_copy)
            bigint_free(result)
            Set result to tmp
        End If
        Set e to e divided by 2
        If e is greater than 0:
            Let sq be bigint_mul(base_copy, base_copy)
            bigint_free(base_copy)
            Set base_copy to sq
        End If
    End While
    bigint_free(base_copy)
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_modular_pow" takes base as Integer, exponent as Integer, modulus as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Computes base^exponent mod modulus using square-and-multiply with
    reduction at every step.  Foundational for RSA, Diffie-Hellman, and
    discrete-log primality tests.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Big-endian bit scan over the exponent.  At each step square the
    accumulator mod modulus; multiply by base mod modulus when the
    current exponent bit is 1.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(bit_length(exponent)) multiplications, each followed by a divmod.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Modulus must be non-zero.  Negative exponents return 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If bigint_is_zero(modulus) is equal to 1:
        Return bigint_from_int64(0)
    End If
    Let exp_neg be bigint_is_negative(exponent)
    If exp_neg is equal to 1:
        Return bigint_from_int64(0)
    End If
    Let result be bigint_from_int64(1)
    Let base_mod be bigint_mod(base, modulus)
    Let bits be bigint_bit_length(exponent)
    Let i be bits minus 1
    While i is greater than -1:
        Let sq be bigint_mul(result, result)
        bigint_free(result)
        Let sq_mod be bigint_mod(sq, modulus)
        bigint_free(sq)
        Set result to sq_mod
        Let bit be bigint_test_bit(exponent, i)
        If bit is equal to 1:
            Let prod be bigint_mul(result, base_mod)
            bigint_free(result)
            Let prod_mod be bigint_mod(prod, modulus)
            bigint_free(prod)
            Set result to prod_mod
        End If
        Set i to i minus 1
    End While
    bigint_free(base_mod)
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_modular_inverse" takes a as Integer, modulus as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns a^(-1) mod modulus when gcd(a, modulus) == 1; otherwise
    returns 0 (no inverse).  Used for RSA private-key recovery and
    finite-field arithmetic.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Extended Euclidean algorithm: track (old_r, r) and (old_s, s) such
    that old_s * a + (something) * modulus = old_r.  When old_r reaches
    1 the inverse is old_s mod modulus.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(log min(|a|, |modulus|)) divmod operations.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Modulus must be > 1.  Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If bigint_is_zero(modulus) is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let old_r be bigint_mod(a, modulus)
    Let r be bigint_copy(modulus)
    Let old_s be bigint_from_int64(1)
    Let s be bigint_from_int64(0)
    While bigint_is_zero(r) is equal to 0:
        Let holder be Layout.allocate(8)
        If holder is equal to 0:
            bigint_free(old_r)
            bigint_free(r)
            bigint_free(old_s)
            bigint_free(s)
            Return 0
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_int64(holder, 0, 0)
        Let q be bigint_divmod(old_r, r, holder)
        Let new_r be Memory.memory_get_int64(holder, 0)
        Layout.deallocate(holder)
        bigint_free(old_r)
        Set old_r to r
        Set r to new_r
        Let qs be bigint_mul(q, s)
        Let new_s be bigint_sub(old_s, qs)
        bigint_free(qs)
        bigint_free(q)
        bigint_free(old_s)
        Set old_s to s
        Set s to new_s
    End While
    bigint_free(r)
    bigint_free(s)
    Let one be bigint_from_int64(1)
    Let cmp be bigint_cmp_magnitude(old_r, one)
    bigint_free(one)
    If cmp is not equal to 0:
        bigint_free(old_r)
        bigint_free(old_s)
        Return 0
    End If
    bigint_free(old_r)
    Let result be bigint_mod(old_s, modulus)
    bigint_free(old_s)
    If bigint_is_negative(result) is equal to 1:
        Let adjusted be bigint_add(result, modulus)
        bigint_free(result)
        Return adjusted
    End If
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_sqrt_floor" takes a as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Integer square root: returns floor(sqrt(|a|)) via Newton's method.
    Returns 0 for negative a.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Newton iteration: x_{n+1} = (x_n + a/x_n) / 2, with an initial
    estimate of 2^ceil(bit_length(a) / 2) so we always start above the
    true root and the iteration is monotonically decreasing.  Terminates
    when x_{n+1} >= x_n.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(log bit_length(a)) iterations, each with a divmod.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.  Negative input returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If bigint_is_negative(a) is equal to 1:
        Return bigint_from_int64(0)
    End If
    If bigint_is_zero(a) is equal to 1:
        Return bigint_from_int64(0)
    End If
    Let one be bigint_from_int64(1)
    Let bits be bigint_bit_length(a)
    Let init_bits be (bits plus 1) divided by 2
    Let x be bigint_shl(one, init_bits)
    bigint_free(one)
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let div_r be bigint_div(a, x)
        Let sum be bigint_add(x, div_r)
        bigint_free(div_r)
        Let two be bigint_from_int64(2)
        Let next be bigint_div(sum, two)
        bigint_free(sum)
        bigint_free(two)
        Let cmp be bigint_cmp(next, x)
        If cmp is greater than -1:
            bigint_free(next)
            Return x
        End If
        bigint_free(x)
        Set x to next
    End While
    Return x
End Process

Process called "bigint_sqrt" takes a as Integer returns Integer:
    Return bigint_sqrt_floor(a)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Decimal and hex string conversion
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "bigint_to_decimal_string" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Converts a BigInt to a freshly-allocated null-terminated decimal
    string.  Negative inputs receive a leading '-' character.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Repeatedly short-divide by 10^9 (largest power of 10 fitting a
    32-bit divisor), generating 9 decimal digits per iteration.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(d) where d = decimal digit count.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If b is equal to 0:
        Let zero_str be Layout.allocate(2)
        If zero_str is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zero_str, 0, 48)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zero_str, 1, 0)
        Return zero_str
    End If
    If bigint_is_zero(b) is equal to 1:
        Let zs be Layout.allocate(2)
        If zs is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zs, 0, 48)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zs, 1, 0)
        Return zs
    End If
    Let bit_len be bigint_bit_length(b)
    Note: ceil(bits * log10(2)) + sign + null + slack; bits/3 + 8 is a safe over-estimate.
    Let max_digits be (bit_len divided by 3) plus 8
    Let digit_buf be Layout.allocate(max_digits)
    If digit_buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_zero(digit_buf, max_digits)
    Let work be bigint_abs(b)
    If work is equal to 0:
        Layout.deallocate(digit_buf)
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pos be 0
    Let rem_holder be Layout.allocate(8)
    If rem_holder is equal to 0:
        bigint_free(work)
        Layout.deallocate(digit_buf)
        Return 0
    End If
    While bigint_is_zero(work) is equal to 0:
        Memory.memory_set_int64(rem_holder, 0, 0)
        Let next_work be bigint_divmod_single_limb(work, 1000000000, rem_holder)
        Let rem be Memory.memory_get_int64(rem_holder, 0)
        bigint_free(work)
        Set work to next_work
        Let chunk_done be 0
        Let chunk_count be 9
        While chunk_done is less than chunk_count:
            Let digit be rem modulo by 10
            Memory.memory_set_byte(digit_buf, pos, digit plus 48)
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Set rem to rem divided by 10
            Set chunk_done to chunk_done plus 1
        End While
    End While
    Layout.deallocate(rem_holder)
    bigint_free(work)
    Note: Strip trailing zeros from the digit buffer (which is reversed).
    While pos is greater than 1:
        If Memory.memory_get_byte(digit_buf, pos minus 1) is not equal to 48:
            Break
        End If
        Set pos to pos minus 1
    End While
    Let is_neg be bigint_is_negative(b)
    Let total_len be pos plus is_neg
    Let out be Layout.allocate(total_len plus 1)
    If out is equal to 0:
        Layout.deallocate(digit_buf)
        Return 0
    End If
    Let write_idx be 0
    If is_neg is equal to 1:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, 0, 45)
        Set write_idx to 1
    End If
    Let i be pos minus 1
    While i is greater than -1:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, write_idx, Memory.memory_get_byte(digit_buf, i))
        Set write_idx to write_idx plus 1
        Set i to i minus 1
    End While
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out, write_idx, 0)
    Layout.deallocate(digit_buf)
    Return out
End Process

Process called "bigint_from_decimal_string" takes str as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parses a null-terminated decimal string into a BigInt.  Accepts an
    optional leading '+' or '-'.  Whitespace and trailing garbage are
    NOT accepted.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Walk the string forward; for each digit compute (result * 10) +
    digit using BigInt arithmetic.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(d^2) due to repeated multiplications by 10; sufficient for
    initialization paths.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    NULL string returns 0; malformed input returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let idx be 0
    Let is_neg be 0
    Let first be Memory.memory_get_byte(str, 0)
    If first is equal to 45:
        Set is_neg to 1
        Set idx to 1
    End If
    If first is equal to 43:
        Set idx to 1
    End If
    Let result be bigint_from_int64(0)
    Let ten be bigint_from_int64(10)
    Let started be 0
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let ch be Memory.memory_get_byte(str, idx)
        If ch is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
        If ch is less than 48:
            bigint_free(result)
            bigint_free(ten)
            Return 0
        End If
        If ch is greater than 57:
            bigint_free(result)
            bigint_free(ten)
            Return 0
        End If
        Let digit be ch minus 48
        Let times_ten be bigint_mul(result, ten)
        bigint_free(result)
        Let dig_bn be bigint_from_int64(digit)
        Let new_result be bigint_add(times_ten, dig_bn)
        bigint_free(times_ten)
        bigint_free(dig_bn)
        Set result to new_result
        Set started to 1
        Set idx to idx plus 1
    End While
    bigint_free(ten)
    If started is equal to 0:
        bigint_free(result)
        Return 0
    End If
    If is_neg is equal to 1:
        Let count be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
        If count is not equal to 0:
            Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, -1)
        End If
    End If
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_to_hex_string" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Renders a BigInt to a lowercase hex string (no "0x" prefix).
    Negative values receive a leading '-'.  Zero renders as "0".
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Emit limbs from top to bottom; the top limb omits leading zero
    nibbles, lower limbs are padded to 16 nibbles.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(limb_count).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If bigint_is_zero(b) is equal to 1:
        Let zs be Layout.allocate(2)
        If zs is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zs, 0, 48)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(zs, 1, 0)
        Return zs
    End If
    Let count be Memory.memory_get_int64(b, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
    Let is_neg be bigint_is_negative(b)
    Let max_len be (count multiplied by 16) plus is_neg plus 1
    Let out be Layout.allocate(max_len)
    If out is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pos be 0
    If is_neg is equal to 1:
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out, 0, 45)
        Set pos to 1
    End If
    Let top_limb be bigint_get_limb(b, count minus 1)
    Let started be 0
    Let nibble_idx be 15
    While nibble_idx is greater than -1:
        Let shift_count be nibble_idx multiplied by 4
        Let nibble be Bitwise.bitwise_and(Bitwise.right_shift_logical(top_limb, shift_count), 15)
        If started is equal to 0:
            If nibble is equal to 0:
                Set nibble_idx to nibble_idx minus 1
                Continue
            End If
            Set started to 1
        End If
        If nibble is less than 10:
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, nibble plus 48)
        Otherwise:
            Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, (nibble minus 10) plus 97)
        End If
        Set pos to pos plus 1
        Set nibble_idx to nibble_idx minus 1
    End While
    Let limb_idx be count minus 2
    While limb_idx is greater than -1:
        Let limb be bigint_get_limb(b, limb_idx)
        Let ni be 15
        While ni is greater than -1:
            Let sc be ni multiplied by 4
            Let nib be Bitwise.bitwise_and(Bitwise.right_shift_logical(limb, sc), 15)
            If nib is less than 10:
                Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, nib plus 48)
            Otherwise:
                Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, (nib minus 10) plus 97)
            End If
            Set pos to pos plus 1
            Set ni to ni minus 1
        End While
        Set limb_idx to limb_idx minus 1
    End While
    Memory.memory_set_byte(out, pos, 0)
    Return out
End Process

Process called "bigint_from_hex_string" takes str as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Parses a hexadecimal string into a BigInt.  Optional leading '+'
    or '-', optional 0x/0X prefix after the sign.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Walk the string; for each hex digit compute (result << 4) | nibble.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(d) where d = hex digit count.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    NULL or malformed input returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If str is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let idx be 0
    Let is_neg be 0
    Let first be Memory.memory_get_byte(str, 0)
    If first is equal to 45:
        Set is_neg to 1
        Set idx to 1
    End If
    If first is equal to 43:
        Set idx to 1
    End If
    Let p0 be Memory.memory_get_byte(str, idx)
    If p0 is equal to 48:
        Let p1 be Memory.memory_get_byte(str, idx plus 1)
        If p1 is equal to 120:
            Set idx to idx plus 2
        End If
        If p1 is equal to 88:
            Set idx to idx plus 2
        End If
    End If
    Let result be bigint_from_int64(0)
    Let digits_seen be 0
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let ch be Memory.memory_get_byte(str, idx)
        If ch is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
        Let nibble be -1
        If ch is greater than 47:
            If ch is less than 58:
                Set nibble to ch minus 48
            End If
        End If
        If nibble is equal to -1:
            If ch is greater than 96:
                If ch is less than 103:
                    Set nibble to (ch minus 97) plus 10
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If nibble is equal to -1:
            If ch is greater than 64:
                If ch is less than 71:
                    Set nibble to (ch minus 65) plus 10
                End If
            End If
        End If
        If nibble is equal to -1:
            bigint_free(result)
            Return 0
        End If
        Let shifted be bigint_shl(result, 4)
        bigint_free(result)
        Let nib_bn be bigint_from_int64(nibble)
        Let combined be bigint_or(shifted, nib_bn)
        bigint_free(shifted)
        bigint_free(nib_bn)
        Set result to combined
        Set digits_seen to digits_seen plus 1
        Set idx to idx plus 1
    End While
    If digits_seen is equal to 0:
        bigint_free(result)
        Return 0
    End If
    If is_neg is equal to 1:
        Let count be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF)
        If count is not equal to 0:
            Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, -1)
        End If
    End If
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Byte-array serialization
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "bigint_to_bytes_be" takes b as Integer, out_buffer as Integer, buffer_size as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Writes the absolute value of b into out_buffer as a big-endian
    byte array of exactly buffer_size bytes.  If the magnitude requires
    more bytes than buffer_size, the high-order bytes are silently
    truncated (caller is responsible for sizing).  Returns the number
    of bytes actually used by the magnitude (which may be > buffer_size).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Iterate buffer_size positions from the end, masking the appropriate
    8-bit slice out of the limb array.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(buffer_size).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    out_buffer must have buffer_size bytes writable.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let bit_len be bigint_bit_length(b)
    Let mag_bytes be (bit_len plus 7) divided by 8
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than buffer_size:
        Let bit_pos be (buffer_size minus 1 minus i) multiplied by 8
        Let limb_idx be bit_pos divided by 64
        Let limb_off be bit_pos modulo by 64
        Let limb be bigint_get_limb(b, limb_idx)
        Let byte_val be Bitwise.bitwise_and(Bitwise.right_shift_logical(limb, limb_off), 255)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, i, byte_val)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return mag_bytes
End Process

Process called "bigint_to_bytes_le" takes b as Integer, out_buffer as Integer, buffer_size as Integer returns Integer:
    Let bit_len be bigint_bit_length(b)
    Let mag_bytes be (bit_len plus 7) divided by 8
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than buffer_size:
        Let bit_pos be i multiplied by 8
        Let limb_idx be bit_pos divided by 64
        Let limb_off be bit_pos modulo by 64
        Let limb be bigint_get_limb(b, limb_idx)
        Let byte_val be Bitwise.bitwise_and(Bitwise.right_shift_logical(limb, limb_off), 255)
        Memory.memory_set_byte(out_buffer, i, byte_val)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return mag_bytes
End Process

Process called "bigint_from_bytes_be" takes buffer as Integer, buffer_size as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Constructs a non-negative BigInt from a big-endian byte buffer of
    the given length.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Allocate a BigInt with enough limbs to hold buffer_size bytes,
    deposit each byte at its bit position via OR.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(buffer_size).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let needed_limbs be (buffer_size plus 7) divided by 8
    If needed_limbs is less than 1:
        Set needed_limbs to 1
    End If
    Let result be bigint_alloc(needed_limbs plus 1)
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than buffer_size:
        Let byte_val be Memory.memory_get_byte(buffer, i)
        Let bit_pos be (buffer_size minus 1 minus i) multiplied by 8
        Let limb_idx be bit_pos divided by 64
        Let limb_off be bit_pos modulo by 64
        Let cur be bigint_get_limb(result, limb_idx)
        Let updated be Bitwise.bitwise_or(cur, Bitwise.left_shift(byte_val, limb_off))
        bigint_set_limb(result, limb_idx, updated)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, needed_limbs)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    bigint_normalize(result)
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_from_bytes_le" takes buffer as Integer, buffer_size as Integer returns Integer:
    Let needed_limbs be (buffer_size plus 7) divided by 8
    If needed_limbs is less than 1:
        Set needed_limbs to 1
    End If
    Let result be bigint_alloc(needed_limbs plus 1)
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than buffer_size:
        Let byte_val be Memory.memory_get_byte(buffer, i)
        Let bit_pos be i multiplied by 8
        Let limb_idx be bit_pos divided by 64
        Let limb_off be bit_pos modulo by 64
        Let cur be bigint_get_limb(result, limb_idx)
        Let updated be Bitwise.bitwise_or(cur, Bitwise.left_shift(byte_val, limb_off))
        bigint_set_limb(result, limb_idx, updated)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, needed_limbs)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    bigint_normalize(result)
    Return result
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Primality testing
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "bigint_is_small_prime" takes b as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Quick deterministic check for tiny primes (2, 3) and small-prime
    divisibility (5, 7, 11, ..., 41).  Used to short-circuit before
    Miller-Rabin probing.  Returns 1 = definitely prime,
    0 = definitely composite, -1 = inconclusive (continue testing).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Compare against 2 and 3 directly, reject even numbers and
    multiples of small primes through trial division.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1) per small-prime check.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let two be bigint_from_int64(2)
    Let cmp_two be bigint_cmp(b, two)
    bigint_free(two)
    If cmp_two is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    If cmp_two is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let three be bigint_from_int64(3)
    Let cmp_three be bigint_cmp(b, three)
    bigint_free(three)
    If cmp_three is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let two_bn be bigint_from_int64(2)
    Let r2 be bigint_mod(b, two_bn)
    bigint_free(two_bn)
    Let is_even be bigint_is_zero(r2)
    bigint_free(r2)
    If is_even is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let small_primes_data be Layout.allocate(8 multiplied by 12)
    If small_primes_data is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(small_primes_data, 0, 3)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(small_primes_data, 8, 5)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(small_primes_data, 16, 7)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(small_primes_data, 24, 11)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(small_primes_data, 32, 13)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(small_primes_data, 40, 17)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(small_primes_data, 48, 19)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(small_primes_data, 56, 23)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(small_primes_data, 64, 29)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(small_primes_data, 72, 31)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(small_primes_data, 80, 37)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(small_primes_data, 88, 41)
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 12:
        Let p be Memory.memory_get_int64(small_primes_data, i multiplied by 8)
        Let p_bn be bigint_from_int64(p)
        Let cmp_p be bigint_cmp(b, p_bn)
        If cmp_p is equal to 0:
            bigint_free(p_bn)
            Layout.deallocate(small_primes_data)
            Return 1
        End If
        Let r be bigint_mod(b, p_bn)
        bigint_free(p_bn)
        Let div_by_p be bigint_is_zero(r)
        bigint_free(r)
        If div_by_p is equal to 1:
            Layout.deallocate(small_primes_data)
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Layout.deallocate(small_primes_data)
    Return -1
End Process

Process called "bigint_witness_random" takes n_minus_3 as Integer, random_source as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Picks a pseudo-random witness in [2, n-2] for Miller-Rabin.  When
    random_source is 0 we use a deterministic spread of small witnesses
    cycled by the round index.  When non-zero, the caller has installed
    an entropy.runa Integer seed that we feed through a simple linear
    congruential generator to produce a value in the desired range.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    LCG style (multiplier 6364136223846793005, increment 1442695040888963407)
    over the bit pattern of random_source, reduced modulo n_minus_3
    then shifted by +2.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1) plus one BigInt modulo against n_minus_3.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    For cryptographic use, the caller MUST supply random_source from
    entropy_random_u64.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let seed be random_source
    Let mul_const be 6364136223846793005
    Let add_const be 1442695040888963407
    Let next_seed be (seed multiplied by mul_const) plus add_const
    Let seed_bn be bigint_from_int64(next_seed)
    Let range be bigint_copy(n_minus_3)
    Let reduced be bigint_mod(seed_bn, range)
    bigint_free(seed_bn)
    bigint_free(range)
    If bigint_is_negative(reduced) is equal to 1:
        Let pos be bigint_negate(reduced)
        bigint_free(reduced)
        Set reduced to pos
    End If
    Let two be bigint_from_int64(2)
    Let result be bigint_add(reduced, two)
    bigint_free(reduced)
    bigint_free(two)
    Return result
End Process

Process called "bigint_miller_rabin" takes n as Integer, rounds as Integer, random_source as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Miller-Rabin probabilistic primality test.  Returns 1 if n is
    probably prime (no witness found after `rounds` iterations), 0 if
    a composite witness was found.  Pre-screens with small-prime trial
    division for fast rejection.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Write n - 1 = 2^s * d with d odd.  For each round, pick a random
    witness a in [2, n - 2] and compute a^d mod n.  If the result is
    1 or n - 1 the witness is non-composite.  Otherwise square it s-1
    more times looking for n - 1; if never found, n is composite.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(rounds * log^3 n).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    For cryptographic primality (e.g. RSA prime generation) callers
    should pass rounds >= 64 and supply real entropy via random_source.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let small_check be bigint_is_small_prime(n)
    If small_check is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If small_check is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let one be bigint_from_int64(1)
    Let n_minus_1 be bigint_sub(n, one)
    bigint_free(one)
    Let two be bigint_from_int64(2)
    Let n_minus_3 be bigint_sub(n_minus_1, two)
    bigint_free(two)
    Let d be bigint_copy(n_minus_1)
    Let s be 0
    Let two_bn be bigint_from_int64(2)
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let r be bigint_mod(d, two_bn)
        Let is_even be bigint_is_zero(r)
        bigint_free(r)
        If is_even is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
        Let new_d be bigint_div(d, two_bn)
        bigint_free(d)
        Set d to new_d
        Set s to s plus 1
    End While
    bigint_free(two_bn)
    Let round_idx be 0
    Let current_random be random_source
    Let composite_found be 0
    While round_idx is less than rounds:
        If composite_found is equal to 1:
            Break
        End If
        Let a be bigint_witness_random(n_minus_3, current_random plus round_idx)
        Let x be bigint_modular_pow(a, d, n)
        bigint_free(a)
        Let cmp_one be 0
        Let one_bn be bigint_from_int64(1)
        Set cmp_one to bigint_cmp(x, one_bn)
        bigint_free(one_bn)
        Let cmp_nm1 be bigint_cmp(x, n_minus_1)
        If cmp_one is equal to 0:
            bigint_free(x)
            Set round_idx to round_idx plus 1
            Continue
        End If
        If cmp_nm1 is equal to 0:
            bigint_free(x)
            Set round_idx to round_idx plus 1
            Continue
        End If
        Let inner be 0
        Let limit be s minus 1
        Let witnessed be 0
        While inner is less than limit:
            Let xsq be bigint_mul(x, x)
            Let xsq_mod be bigint_mod(xsq, n)
            bigint_free(xsq)
            bigint_free(x)
            Set x to xsq_mod
            Let cmp_b be bigint_cmp(x, n_minus_1)
            If cmp_b is equal to 0:
                Set witnessed to 1
                Break
            End If
            Set inner to inner plus 1
        End While
        bigint_free(x)
        If witnessed is equal to 0:
            Set composite_found to 1
        End If
        Set round_idx to round_idx plus 1
    End While
    bigint_free(d)
    bigint_free(n_minus_1)
    bigint_free(n_minus_3)
    If composite_found is equal to 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "bigint_is_prime_bpsw" takes n as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Baillie-PSW primality test: a Miller-Rabin base-2 test followed by
    a strong Lucas test.  No known composite has ever been found that
    passes BPSW, making it deterministic for all 64-bit integers and
    extremely strong on larger inputs.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Phase 1: trial division (via bigint_is_small_prime).
    Phase 2: Miller-Rabin with witness a = 2.
    Phase 3: strong Lucas test using Selfridge's parameter selection
             D = 5, -7, 9, -11, ... such that the Jacobi symbol (D/n)
             equals -1; P = 1, Q = (1 - D) / 4.  Then test U_d and V_d
             where d is the odd part of n + 1.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(log^3 n) bit operations.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Returns 0 for n < 2 and for any n that fails either phase.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let small_check be bigint_is_small_prime(n)
    If small_check is equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    If small_check is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let one be bigint_from_int64(1)
    Let n_minus_1 be bigint_sub(n, one)
    bigint_free(one)
    Let d be bigint_copy(n_minus_1)
    Let s be 0
    Let two_bn be bigint_from_int64(2)
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let r be bigint_mod(d, two_bn)
        Let is_even be bigint_is_zero(r)
        bigint_free(r)
        If is_even is equal to 0:
            Break
        End If
        Let new_d be bigint_div(d, two_bn)
        bigint_free(d)
        Set d to new_d
        Set s to s plus 1
    End While
    Let x be bigint_modular_pow(two_bn, d, n)
    bigint_free(two_bn)
    Let one_bn be bigint_from_int64(1)
    Let cmp_one be bigint_cmp(x, one_bn)
    bigint_free(one_bn)
    Let cmp_nm1 be bigint_cmp(x, n_minus_1)
    Let mr_passed be 0
    If cmp_one is equal to 0:
        Set mr_passed to 1
    End If
    If cmp_nm1 is equal to 0:
        Set mr_passed to 1
    End If
    If mr_passed is equal to 0:
        Let inner be 0
        Let limit be s minus 1
        While inner is less than limit:
            Let xsq be bigint_mul(x, x)
            Let xsq_mod be bigint_mod(xsq, n)
            bigint_free(xsq)
            bigint_free(x)
            Set x to xsq_mod
            Let cmp_b be bigint_cmp(x, n_minus_1)
            If cmp_b is equal to 0:
                Set mr_passed to 1
                Break
            End If
            Set inner to inner plus 1
        End While
    End If
    bigint_free(x)
    bigint_free(d)
    bigint_free(n_minus_1)
    If mr_passed is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Note: Strong Lucas test with Selfridge parameter selection.
    Let n_sqrt be bigint_sqrt_floor(n)
    Let sqrt_sq be bigint_mul(n_sqrt, n_sqrt)
    Let is_square be bigint_cmp(sqrt_sq, n)
    bigint_free(sqrt_sq)
    bigint_free(n_sqrt)
    If is_square is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "bigint_random" takes bit_length as Integer, random_source as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Generates a uniformly-distributed non-negative BigInt with exactly
    bit_length significant bits.  The top bit is forced to 1 so that
    the magnitude actually fills the requested width.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Pull random 64-bit words from a deterministic seeded LCG keyed on
    random_source (the caller's entropy.runa Integer seed).  Fill the
    requested limb count, mask off excess bits in the top limb, and
    set the top bit.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(bit_length / 64) PRNG iterations.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Caller MUST supply random_source from entropy.entropy_random_u64
    for cryptographic-grade randomness.  When random_source is 0 the
    output is reproducible but not cryptographically random.
    @End Security_Scope

    If bit_length is less than 1:
        Return bigint_from_int64(0)
    End If
    Let limb_count be (bit_length plus 63) divided by 64
    Let result be bigint_alloc(limb_count plus 1)
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let mul_const be 6364136223846793005
    Let add_const be 1442695040888963407
    Let state be random_source
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than limb_count:
        Set state to (state multiplied by mul_const) plus add_const
        bigint_set_limb(result, i, state)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_LIMB_COUNT_OFF, limb_count)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(result, BIGINT_SIGN_OFF, 1)
    Let top_bits_in_high_limb be bit_length modulo by 64
    If top_bits_in_high_limb is not equal to 0:
        Let mask be Bitwise.left_shift(1, top_bits_in_high_limb) minus 1
        Let top be bigint_get_limb(result, limb_count minus 1)
        bigint_set_limb(result, limb_count minus 1, Bitwise.bitwise_and(top, mask))
    End If
    Let bit_in_limb be (bit_length minus 1) modulo by 64
    Let limb_for_top be (bit_length minus 1) divided by 64
    Let top_now be bigint_get_limb(result, limb_for_top)
    bigint_set_limb(result, limb_for_top, Bitwise.bitwise_or(top_now, Bitwise.left_shift(1, bit_in_limb)))
    bigint_normalize(result)
    Return result
End Process
